data.Generated_facility_notes_full_text:
The state provides facility-level cumulative data. The state does not provide facility-level outbreak data. Cumulative facility-level data was first reported by the state on 2020-05-14. 

Because each state reports facility-level data differently, CTP has produced a number of scripts to make the dataset as standardized and comprehensive as possible. This state uses the following scripts: post_processing, standardize_data. More information on each of these scripts can be found in our Airtable Facility Script Annotations. (https://airtable.com/shr99Ep06cplrcVg6)
data.Public_Notes:
Washington, DC reports long-term-care data for Skilled Nursing facilities and Assisted-Living facilities. COVID Tracking Project puts Skilled Nursing facility data in the Nursing Home category, and Assisted-Living facility data in the Assisted Living category. DC reports cumulative data but not outbreak data. Data is cumulative since March 2020. 
 
Washington, DC provides facility-level data for Skilled Nursing Facilities and Assisted Living Facilities. Washington, DC reports staff and resident cases and staff and resident deaths separately. 
 
CTP does not include "Hospital for Sick Children LTC" in totals for facility count, cases, and deaths. Assisted Living data does not appear in our dataset until December 10, 2020.
 
- July 2, 2020: Washington, DC didn’t report long-term care data. CTP carried over totals from June 25, 2020.
- August 27, 2020: Washington, DC reported a decrease in cumulative totals for resident positives, staff positives, and facilities.
- November 26, 2020: Washington, DC reported a decrease in cumulative totals for staff deaths by 1.
- December 3, 2020: Cumulative resident deaths decreased from 163 to 159.
- December 10, 2020: Washington, DC started reporting long-term care data for Assisted Living Facilities.
- February 18, 2021: Nursing homes resident cases decreased by 27.
data.Alert_Message: CTP does not include "Hospital for Sick Children LTC" in totals for facility count, cases, and deaths.
